WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:01.269
.

00:05.706 --> 00:06.607
(Male announcer)
In the criminal justice system,

00:08.676 --> 00:12.180
sexually based offenses are
considered especially heinous.

00:12.213 --> 00:14.615
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:14.648 --> 00:16.584
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:16.617 --> 00:18.119
are members of an elite squad

00:18.152 --> 00:20.088
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:20.121 --> 00:22.290
These are their stories.

00:29.197 --> 00:31.732
Tonight on
America's Worst Crimes...

00:31.765 --> 00:34.168
We've heard
these stories before.

00:34.202 --> 00:37.371
A vicious rape on campus,
an unresponsive university.

00:37.405 --> 00:40.074
And yet, the details
of this particular story

00:40.108 --> 00:42.376
are even more horrifying
than usual.

00:44.212 --> 00:45.679
Just steps away
from the hectic heart

00:45.713 --> 00:49.750
of New York City
stands Hudson University,

00:49.783 --> 00:52.353
a venerable institution
of higher learning.

00:52.386 --> 00:54.422
A sanctuary of the mind.

00:54.455 --> 00:57.091
For a freshman--
we'll call her Jane--

00:57.125 --> 01:00.461
away from her small Midwestern
hometown for the first time,

01:00.494 --> 01:05.333
New York City and Hudson
were a dream come true.

01:05.366 --> 01:08.536
But Jane's dream was about
to turn into a nightmare.

01:09.703 --> 01:11.505
It started out
innocently enough.

01:11.539 --> 01:13.574
Bill was a popular athlete

01:13.607 --> 01:16.144
who seemed like
real boyfriend material.

01:17.245 --> 01:19.513
I thought he was
one of the good guys.

01:19.547 --> 01:21.815
But you were wrong.

01:21.849 --> 01:24.452
About everything.

01:24.485 --> 01:26.187
(Skip)
They went back to his room

01:26.220 --> 01:29.157
in one of the most popular
fraternities on campus.

01:33.194 --> 01:35.329
What started
as a romantic moment

01:35.363 --> 01:37.698
quickly took
a terrifying turn.

01:39.367 --> 01:41.502
Jane suddenly found herself
outnumbered

01:41.535 --> 01:44.238
by four men twice her size,

01:44.272 --> 01:46.707
all with malicious
intentions.

01:46.740 --> 01:50.144
I could not believe
he'd do this to me.

01:50.178 --> 01:53.181
(Skip)
But he did, didn't he?

01:53.214 --> 01:56.150
He set the whole attack up.

01:56.184 --> 01:58.752
And he gave his three friends
permission

01:58.786 --> 02:01.655
to do whatever
they wanted?

02:02.723 --> 02:05.293
(Jane)
At some point I just went numb.

02:05.326 --> 02:07.361
(Skip)
She was viciously gang-raped
for hours.

02:07.395 --> 02:09.797
Her anguished cries
for help went unanswered.

02:09.830 --> 02:11.699
No! No!

02:13.434 --> 02:17.271
I could tell
I wasn't even human to them.

02:17.305 --> 02:19.740
They took turns raping you.

02:19.773 --> 02:21.275
Yes.

02:21.309 --> 02:23.277
Sodomizing you.

02:23.311 --> 02:25.179
Yes.

02:27.315 --> 02:29.317
When they were done,
they...

02:29.350 --> 02:31.319
Okay, Noah,
just to be clear,

02:31.352 --> 02:33.487
you are not going
to Hudson University.

02:33.521 --> 02:35.289
No, no.
What do you want?

02:35.323 --> 02:36.757
(Skip)
I know this is difficult.

02:36.790 --> 02:37.925
Here you go, sweetie.

02:37.958 --> 02:40.728
They called me a whore.

02:40.761 --> 02:42.696
They called me a slut.

02:43.997 --> 02:46.800
They shoved me out of the door
like I was garbage.

02:48.302 --> 02:50.504
Did you call the police
or campus security?

02:50.538 --> 02:53.374
When I was up to it,
I went to the school.

02:55.609 --> 02:58.479
They asked me
if I had been drinking,

02:58.512 --> 03:01.315
if anyone could
corroborate.

03:01.349 --> 03:02.316
[phone rings]
Milk?

03:02.350 --> 03:03.517
(Jane)
They made me feel like

03:03.551 --> 03:05.553
I'd made a bad decision that
night, and it was my fault.

03:05.586 --> 03:08.256
Chief Dodds.

03:08.289 --> 03:10.824
America's Worst Crimes?
I'm actually just watching it.

03:10.858 --> 03:13.193
Uh, no, I-I hadn't
heard about it.

03:14.695 --> 03:17.231
[mutes TV]
The mayor's wife was watching?

03:17.265 --> 03:19.900
Well, that's just terrific.

03:19.933 --> 03:22.002
Yup.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.437
We're on it.

03:25.906 --> 03:29.910
But for Jane,
her ordeal had only just begun.

03:29.943 --> 03:33.314
More from this nightmare
on campus when we return.

03:35.783 --> 03:37.318
[sighs]

03:38.719 --> 03:41.689
[dramatic music]

04:24.298 --> 04:25.198
But for Jane,
her ordeal had only just begun.

04:26.066 --> 04:27.701
More from this--
[mutes TV]

04:27.735 --> 04:28.669
[groans]

04:28.702 --> 04:30.904
This is what you do
with your Sundays off?

04:30.938 --> 04:32.940
Me and Gracie Mansion,
apparently.

04:32.973 --> 04:34.041
And now, 1PP is pissed

04:34.074 --> 04:36.544
because they got caught
flat-footed on national TV.

04:36.577 --> 04:38.746
America's Worst Crimes
has a huge following.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.382
This is gonna go viral.
(Carisi) Yeah, I looked into it.

04:41.415 --> 04:42.950
The report says the attack
happened in December,

04:42.983 --> 04:44.852
but NYPD's got no record
of a complaint

04:44.885 --> 04:46.320
from the vic or Hudson U.

04:46.354 --> 04:48.656
She did say that Hudson
University ignored her.

04:48.689 --> 04:50.391
And God knows we've been
down that road before.

04:50.424 --> 04:52.092
I know that the tail
wags the dog,

04:52.125 --> 04:54.061
but these TV shows are in it
for the ratings.

04:54.094 --> 04:55.896
We don't know that
any of this even happened.

04:55.929 --> 04:57.030
(Carisi)
Yeah, I'm all for overtime,

04:57.064 --> 04:58.699
but don't we have
enough work to do?

04:58.732 --> 05:00.368
Guys, this isn't LMZ.

05:00.401 --> 05:02.936
It is a legitimate
national news magazine.

05:02.970 --> 05:05.105
They interviewed her.
She disclosed.

05:05.138 --> 05:07.375
And I got a call
from Dodds,

05:07.408 --> 05:09.076
who got a call
from the mayor.

05:09.109 --> 05:11.445
So we are going
to investigate.

05:11.479 --> 05:13.414
(Rollins)
We don't even know
who this girl is.

05:13.447 --> 05:14.615
America's Worst Crimes does.

05:14.648 --> 05:16.950
Don't make me talk
to reporters.

05:19.119 --> 05:20.888
(Skip)
Detectives.

05:20.921 --> 05:22.590
I'm guessing you're here
about the Hudson story.

05:22.623 --> 05:24.358
Yeah, well, you got
everybody talking,

05:24.392 --> 05:26.394
- including our bosses.
- Well, that's gratifying.

05:26.427 --> 05:29.397
And not just the Peabody buzz,
but for AWC to be in a position

05:29.430 --> 05:31.865
to amplify what's going on
behind those ivy walls.

05:31.899 --> 05:34.034
Yeah, well, you amplify,
we investigate.

05:34.067 --> 05:36.036
So we're going to need
to talk to Jane.

05:36.069 --> 05:37.705
Well, I'd love to help,

05:37.738 --> 05:39.106
especially with what that girl
had to suffer through.

05:39.139 --> 05:40.774
But I can't give you
her name.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.610
Your report says
she was gang-raped.

05:42.643 --> 05:44.478
Now's not the time to hide
behind the First Amendment.

05:44.512 --> 05:46.447
I'm not falling
on my journalistic sword.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.949
The only way Jane would talk
was if I promised her anonymity.

05:48.982 --> 05:51.084
She's scared to death
of those fraternity boys.

05:51.118 --> 05:52.720
We can find a judge
who will compel you

05:52.753 --> 05:54.588
to hand over your sources
and raw footage.

05:54.622 --> 05:56.790
All right, look, I'll kick
the footage request upstairs.

05:56.824 --> 05:58.125
That's not my call.

05:58.158 --> 06:00.027
As for Jane,
I can put you in touch

06:00.060 --> 06:02.129
with the woman
who shopped me the story.

06:02.162 --> 06:05.132
Maybe she can convince Jane
to talk to NYPD.

06:05.165 --> 06:07.635
Come on.

06:10.538 --> 06:11.972
(Dillon)
Really insightful work, Emma.

06:12.005 --> 06:13.807
(Rollins)
Professor Dillon? Hey.

06:13.841 --> 06:16.744
Detectives Rollins
and Detective Carisi.

06:16.777 --> 06:18.178
We're from SVU.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.813
- How can I help?
- We just, um...

06:19.847 --> 06:21.449
We wanted to talk to you
for a minute

06:21.482 --> 06:23.717
about the AWC segment
last night.

06:23.751 --> 06:26.587
Sure. I thought it was
important, what they did.

06:26.620 --> 06:28.556
I'm glad they started
the dialogue.

06:28.589 --> 06:29.990
Hey, listen, we were hoping
that you could

06:30.023 --> 06:31.759
get us in touch
with--with Jane.

06:31.792 --> 06:33.427
The reporter said
you introduced them.

06:33.461 --> 06:35.829
I thought it was crucial
her story be heard.

06:35.863 --> 06:40.434
But Jane already tried to
disclose once, to the school.

06:40.468 --> 06:41.368
You heard
how that turned out.

06:41.401 --> 06:43.537
Look, whatever happened
between the victim--

06:43.571 --> 06:44.805
Survivor.

06:44.838 --> 06:46.073
Okay, the survivor
and the university,

06:46.106 --> 06:47.508
that's got nothing
to do with us.

06:47.541 --> 06:48.876
You have to understand,

06:48.909 --> 06:50.744
this woman is still
extremely fragile.

06:50.778 --> 06:52.580
To subject her
to harsh scrutiny,

06:52.613 --> 06:54.748
- the legal system...
- All due respect, Professor,

06:54.782 --> 06:56.116
obviously we'd like
to go through you,

06:56.149 --> 06:57.618
but if you're just gonna
get in the way,

06:57.651 --> 06:59.487
we'll go over
or around you.

06:59.520 --> 07:02.656
Interesting phallocentric choice
of language, Detective.

07:02.690 --> 07:05.993
My partner is
still a work in progress.

07:06.026 --> 07:09.697
Listen, we all know
that something terrible

07:09.730 --> 07:11.699
happened to Jane.

07:11.732 --> 07:13.867
We don't want these guys
to get away with it.

07:13.901 --> 07:15.869
I hear you.
I do.

07:15.903 --> 07:20.708
I just don't think that Jane
wants to deal with any of this.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.876
But I'll give her a call.

07:25.012 --> 07:27.147
I see.

07:27.180 --> 07:29.216
All right,
thank you very much.

07:31.284 --> 07:32.686
[sighs]

07:32.720 --> 07:34.187
That was Professor Dillon.

07:34.221 --> 07:36.256
Jane says she's not
going to talk to us.

07:36.289 --> 07:39.560
That she'll come forward
when and where she wants.

07:39.593 --> 07:40.894
What does that mean?

07:40.928 --> 07:42.563
She's scared to make
an official complaint.

07:42.596 --> 07:43.864
And knowing what we know,

07:43.897 --> 07:45.799
I can't blame her.

07:45.833 --> 07:47.635
So that leaves us where?

07:47.668 --> 07:49.036
Back at square one.

07:49.069 --> 07:51.171
Dillon's no help.

07:51.204 --> 07:53.173
Hey, speaking of which,

07:53.206 --> 07:56.143
what was that crack about me
still being a work in progress?

07:56.176 --> 07:58.946
Oh, come on, Carisi.
The lady's a rape advocate.

07:58.979 --> 08:01.148
She's got a chip
about male detectives.

08:01.181 --> 08:04.985
I figured I could earn her trust
if I align myself with her.

08:05.018 --> 08:07.120
Hmm. Rape advocate.

08:07.154 --> 08:08.789
I don't even get
what that is.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.290
I mean, there's
no burglary advocate.

08:10.323 --> 08:12.092
There's no carjacking
advocates.

08:13.627 --> 08:15.629
When's the last time
a carjacking victim got asked,

08:15.663 --> 08:17.965
"Are you sure you didn't want
your car to get stolen?"

08:17.998 --> 08:19.800
Okay, I get that.

08:19.833 --> 08:21.301
- Hmm.
- All right.

08:21.334 --> 08:22.903
But still,
she's just getting in our way.

08:22.936 --> 08:25.939
Yeah, well, that's SVU.
Get used to it.

08:29.943 --> 08:32.145
- Where are you going?
- Back to campus.

08:32.179 --> 08:34.948
I don't want to tell the sarge
we came up empty-handed.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.151
[speaking Italian]

08:39.687 --> 08:41.689
No comment.

08:41.722 --> 08:43.824
Yes.

08:43.857 --> 08:45.158
Okay, good.

08:45.192 --> 08:46.860
Grazie, ciao.

08:46.894 --> 08:49.162
No comment to the Italian press?
They're on this already?

08:49.196 --> 08:51.765
I got to tell you, bad news
in New York travels fast.

08:51.799 --> 08:54.568
I mean, there are
already Twitter campaigns,

08:54.602 --> 08:58.105
calls for campus rallies
and revoking the frat's charter.

08:58.138 --> 09:00.340
Which explains why the mayor
and the D.A. are all over this.

09:00.373 --> 09:01.609
And me.

09:01.642 --> 09:03.777
So have you managed
to ID Jane yet?

09:03.811 --> 09:05.178
Look, Carisi's still trying,

09:05.212 --> 09:07.047
but the closest he
and Rollins have gotten

09:07.080 --> 09:11.051
is Jane's self-proclaimed
advocate, Professor Dillon.

09:11.084 --> 09:12.786
She's going to produce Jane?

09:12.820 --> 09:14.722
No.

09:14.755 --> 09:16.757
Look, Jane is scared
of fraternity retribution

09:16.790 --> 09:18.058
if she goes public.

09:18.091 --> 09:20.093
And she doesn't
trust the police.

09:20.127 --> 09:21.629
So she's not going to talk?

09:21.662 --> 09:23.931
I could subpoena the show
or this professor.

09:23.964 --> 09:26.066
There's got to be
an easier way.

09:26.099 --> 09:27.768
Jane said on the AWC piece

09:27.801 --> 09:29.637
that she disclosed
to the university.

09:29.670 --> 09:31.371
But they didn't
specify to whom.

09:31.404 --> 09:34.074
So let's go to the top
and find out.

09:34.107 --> 09:35.375
Okay. You want me
to come with?

09:35.408 --> 09:36.744
Not necessary.

09:36.777 --> 09:39.246
President Roberts and I
have history.

09:42.683 --> 09:45.118
I'm assuming this is about
that broadcast?

09:45.152 --> 09:46.654
It is.

09:46.687 --> 09:48.822
So the victim said
that she was shut down

09:48.856 --> 09:50.390
by the university.

09:50.423 --> 09:51.825
Do you know
who she spoke to?

09:51.859 --> 09:53.794
- I do. She spoke to me.
- Oh.

09:53.827 --> 09:55.763
I followed
the Department of Education

09:55.796 --> 09:58.265
sexual assault protocols
to the letter.

09:58.298 --> 09:59.800
And yet,
here we are

09:59.833 --> 10:02.235
investigating
an unreported gang-rape

10:02.269 --> 10:04.004
that occurred
on your watch.

10:04.037 --> 10:06.139
The first I heard of
any gang was on that show.

10:06.173 --> 10:07.708
When she came to me,

10:07.741 --> 10:09.176
she mentioned
only one individual.

10:09.209 --> 10:12.079
- And who was that?
- I'm not at liberty to say.

10:12.112 --> 10:13.714
These reports
are confidential.

10:13.747 --> 10:15.348
It's university policy.

10:15.382 --> 10:19.920
That anonymity ceases to exist
when a crime has been committed.

10:19.953 --> 10:21.822
What exactly
did she say?

10:21.855 --> 10:24.191
What she described was
regrettable drunken sex.

10:24.224 --> 10:25.392
Not rape.

10:25.425 --> 10:27.661
With four men
holding her down?

10:27.695 --> 10:30.263
She mentioned
one student only.

10:30.297 --> 10:32.733
She admitted
she was intoxicated.

10:32.766 --> 10:36.369
She went willingly back
to the fraternity with her date.

10:36.403 --> 10:38.972
I asked her whether she was sure
the sex wasn't consensual.

10:39.006 --> 10:41.208
She proceeded
to become defensive,

10:41.241 --> 10:42.710
and then she
left my office.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.878
And you didn't bother
to talk to her "date"?

10:44.912 --> 10:46.379
Actually, I did.

10:46.413 --> 10:48.682
He said the sex
was consensual.

10:48.716 --> 10:51.151
He seemed credible,
he's well-regarded,

10:51.184 --> 10:53.020
and has no prior
complaints.

10:53.053 --> 10:55.022
That was that.

10:55.055 --> 10:56.423
The next I heard of this
was last night

10:56.456 --> 10:58.692
when we were blindsided
on national television.

10:58.726 --> 11:00.460
Well, now that these
allegations have been made,

11:00.493 --> 11:02.863
I will need her name
and the name of the student

11:02.896 --> 11:04.765
that she claims
attacked her.

11:04.798 --> 11:06.767
(Protesters)
We are all Jane!

11:06.800 --> 11:09.703
We are all Jane!
We are all Jane!

11:09.737 --> 11:11.471
So...

11:11.504 --> 11:13.907
she hasn't come to you.

11:13.941 --> 11:15.709
Which means,
whatever happened,

11:15.743 --> 11:18.211
she hasn't filed
a criminal complaint,

11:18.245 --> 11:20.213
which means
my responsibility remains

11:20.247 --> 11:24.051
protecting the confidentiality
of both students.

11:24.084 --> 11:25.753
(Protesters)
We are all Jane!

11:25.786 --> 11:28.455
We are all Jane!
We are all Jane!

11:28.488 --> 11:30.423
We are all Jane!

11:30.457 --> 11:33.961
We are all Jane!
We are all Jane!

11:33.994 --> 11:35.929
Excuse me.

11:35.963 --> 11:38.766
I have a firestorm
on my hands.

11:38.799 --> 11:39.900
(Protesters)
We are all Jane!

11:39.933 --> 11:41.401
We are all Jane!

11:41.434 --> 11:43.771
- Hey, Sarge.
- Hey.

11:43.804 --> 11:45.906
So far on campus
nobody's been any help.

11:45.939 --> 11:47.775
Get anywhere
with President Roberts?

11:47.808 --> 11:49.142
You know,
it's the usual.

11:49.176 --> 11:51.411
First she blames
the victim a little bit,

11:51.444 --> 11:53.480
and then she hides
behind the cloak

11:53.513 --> 11:55.282
of protecting the students'
confidentiality.

11:55.315 --> 11:57.084
So we still don't even know
who the girl is?

11:57.117 --> 11:59.519
- No idea.
(girl) I was told that

11:59.552 --> 12:02.222
if my rapist made me
feel uncomfortable,

12:02.255 --> 12:06.760
I could switch classes
or move to another dorm.

12:06.794 --> 12:09.496
I kept my mouth shut,

12:09.529 --> 12:12.966
and he graduated
with honors last June.

12:14.802 --> 12:16.169
Now, for the first time,

12:16.203 --> 12:19.873
I'm speaking my truth,
because of Jane.

12:19.907 --> 12:21.809
[crowd cheering]

12:25.078 --> 12:26.546
Thank you.

12:26.579 --> 12:30.083
All your stories
have been so powerful.

12:30.117 --> 12:34.454
There is one last survivor
who wants to share her story.

12:34.487 --> 12:38.425
She's someone
you already know.

12:38.458 --> 12:40.460
[crowd cheering]

12:47.300 --> 12:48.869
Hi.

12:48.902 --> 12:52.405
Um, my name
is Heather Manning.

12:56.609 --> 12:58.245
I-I am the real Jane.

13:07.420 --> 13:10.023
I want to tell you my story.

13:11.191 --> 13:12.860
So much for anonymity.

13:12.893 --> 13:14.461
Yeah.

13:22.836 --> 13:23.203
(Benson)
Heather.

13:24.404 --> 13:26.473
Thank you so much
for coming in.

13:26.506 --> 13:29.609
I hope you realize this does not
mean we're pressing charges.

13:29.642 --> 13:32.345
- "We"?
- You know, Professor Dillon,

13:32.379 --> 13:34.848
we think it's probably best
if we speak with Heather alone.

13:34.882 --> 13:37.250
Actually, Sergeant,
could you and I talk?

13:37.284 --> 13:38.952
Um, sure.

13:38.986 --> 13:40.420
- Okay.
- This way.

13:40.453 --> 13:42.956
We just--we just want to get
Heather's side of the story.

13:42.990 --> 13:46.159
(Dillon)
I was worried about bringing
Heather to the police,

13:46.193 --> 13:48.428
being re-traumatized.

13:48.461 --> 13:50.931
But I've spoken to others
in the community,

13:50.964 --> 13:52.565
and they've all said
that if anyone's

13:52.599 --> 13:55.035
going to protect
a survivor, it's you.

13:55.068 --> 13:58.939
I will. And I promise you
that I will look after her.

13:58.972 --> 14:02.109
Heather was clear about
wanting me to sit in with her.

14:02.142 --> 14:04.477
She doesn't know you,
but she trusts me.

14:06.914 --> 14:09.382
December 12th.
I was on a date

14:09.416 --> 14:11.919
with an Alpha Zeta Pi
hockey player.

