27:04.256 --> 27:06.325
But, Heather,
last night at the rally,

27:06.358 --> 27:09.428
you said that there were
six assailants.

27:09.461 --> 27:12.064
Are there two others
that we should be looking for?

27:12.098 --> 27:13.766
Look, I don't know exactly
what happened in that room.

27:13.800 --> 27:15.434
People were hiding
in the shadows,

27:15.467 --> 27:17.003
chanting, throwing things.

27:17.036 --> 27:19.171
- But the four you named--
- Absolutely raped me.

27:19.205 --> 27:20.940
Brian, Connor,
Lance, and Zach.

27:20.973 --> 27:22.441
I-I know Zach was there, because
they kept calling him Stinky,

27:22.474 --> 27:24.310
and he said,
"Dudes, my name is Zach."

27:24.343 --> 27:26.779
(Dillon)
Can I ask why Zach
wasn't picked up?

27:26.813 --> 27:29.181
Because he's in Cuba,
and they won't extradite.

27:29.215 --> 27:31.117
But we do have a warrant
out for his arrest.

27:31.150 --> 27:34.687
Good. And again,
I hope, going forward,

27:34.721 --> 27:37.289
that we can kick apart
their stories, not Heather's.

27:37.323 --> 27:38.858
(Benson)
We can, and we will.

27:38.891 --> 27:40.827
And I hope, going forward,

27:40.860 --> 27:43.462
Heather, that you'll stop
talking to the press

27:43.495 --> 27:46.733
and at rallies about this,
so we can do our job.

27:46.766 --> 27:48.467
You understand?

27:48.500 --> 27:50.770
There's only one problem
with that.

27:50.803 --> 27:52.939
Which is what?

27:52.972 --> 27:54.340
I'm supposed to go
on Anderson Cooper

27:54.373 --> 27:56.242
and Rachel Maddow tonight.

27:58.044 --> 27:59.712
Heather, you're going
to have to cancel those.

27:59.746 --> 28:01.413
(Dillon)
That's impossible.

28:01.447 --> 28:03.282
It's--it's too late.

28:03.315 --> 28:05.952
These issues are finally being
brought to national attention.

28:05.985 --> 28:08.855
The whole country is waking up

28:08.888 --> 28:10.790
to the rape epidemic
on our campuses.

28:10.823 --> 28:12.759
I thought that you said
that you wanted

28:12.792 --> 28:14.727
to bring your assailants
to justice.

28:14.761 --> 28:16.128
I did say that. I do.

28:16.162 --> 28:19.298
But this is so much more
than that now.

28:19.331 --> 28:21.801
I'm the face of a movement.

28:26.773 --> 28:29.742
She wants me to cancel
the interviews.

28:29.776 --> 28:30.676
(Fin) How'd that go?
- Not good.

28:30.709 --> 28:33.412
- She wants her story heard.
- Which one?

28:33.445 --> 28:35.314
Her story's
falling apart.

28:35.347 --> 28:37.817
Six guys, four guys,
hockey sticks, no DNA.

28:37.850 --> 28:40.386
She keeps talking, she's going
to torpedo her own case.

28:40.419 --> 28:42.822
(Fin)
Zach Franklin just surfaced
at his lawyer's office.

28:42.855 --> 28:45.291
He's about to go live
on LMZ right now.

28:45.324 --> 28:47.493
Folks, just let me know
when you're all ready,

28:47.526 --> 28:48.828
and we'll get this going.

28:48.861 --> 28:51.263
Hey, Liv, you know
about this?

28:51.297 --> 28:53.499
I'm John Buchanan,
attorney for Zach Franklin.

28:53.532 --> 28:55.401
Star athlete, scholar,

28:55.434 --> 28:58.304
and unequivocally innocent
of any and all charges

28:58.337 --> 29:00.840
in the so-called
Hudson University gang-rape.

29:00.873 --> 29:02.208
Of course he is.

29:02.241 --> 29:04.243
That's a big bluff,
even for Buchanan.

29:04.276 --> 29:05.878
Think he's got something?

29:05.912 --> 29:08.815
Tell them where you were
December 12th, 2014,

29:08.848 --> 29:12.151
the night of Heather Manning's
alleged assault.

29:12.184 --> 29:15.187
I was nine hours away,
in Kimball, West Virginia,

29:15.221 --> 29:17.189
on the W.V. Hillmen
soccer field.

29:19.125 --> 29:21.560
The championship game
was televised live

29:21.593 --> 29:24.797
on SEN until 11:40 p.m.
Eastern time.

29:24.831 --> 29:26.799
If you missed it,

29:26.833 --> 29:28.835
you'll be happy to hear
Hudson won, 3-zip.

29:28.868 --> 29:30.937
- Benson.
- We didn't vet this?

29:30.970 --> 29:33.806
He was in Cuba, Barba.
Remember?

29:33.840 --> 29:35.908
(Buchanan)
This was the exact time
Heather Manning

29:35.942 --> 29:38.077
was alleging my client

29:38.110 --> 29:41.948
was engaged in a heinous crime
against her.

29:41.981 --> 29:46.953
NYPD and the D.A. are
guilty of an outrageous

29:57.830 --> 29:58.831
Zach, tell them where you were
December 12th, 2014,

30:00.867 --> 30:02.401
the night of Heather Manning's
alleged assault.

30:02.434 --> 30:06.538
I was nine hours away,
in Kimball, West Virginia,

30:06.572 --> 30:08.540
on the W.V. Hillmen
soccer field.

30:08.574 --> 30:11.343
"Alleged assault"?
Heather was gang-raped.

30:11.377 --> 30:14.180
If that's true, Zach Franklin
was not involved.

30:14.213 --> 30:15.447
I could have sworn
he was there.

30:15.481 --> 30:17.850
It was dark,
but I heard his voice.

30:17.884 --> 30:19.986
Because you told us that they
called him by his nickname,

30:20.019 --> 30:22.989
that you heard him respond.

30:23.022 --> 30:25.124
Well, maybe that happened
in a nightmare.

30:25.157 --> 30:26.859
I haven't been sleeping.

30:26.893 --> 30:28.560
(Dillon)
Survivors have unclear memories.

30:28.594 --> 30:31.630
But the other boys are guilty.
You have their DNA.

30:31.663 --> 30:33.165
They're claiming
it was consensual.

30:33.199 --> 30:35.334
And you believe them
over Heather?

30:35.367 --> 30:37.636
Professor Dillon,
I think it's best

30:37.669 --> 30:39.171
if Heather speaks
to the A.D.A. alone.

30:39.205 --> 30:40.306
I disagree.

30:40.339 --> 30:42.241
I'm the only one
who's been here for her.

30:42.274 --> 30:43.910
(Barba)
You've advocated enough.
It's our turn.

30:43.943 --> 30:46.946
If you want this case
to continue,

30:46.979 --> 30:48.414
I need Heather to tell me
exactly what happened to her.

30:48.447 --> 30:50.016
And you need to tell
Detective Rollins

30:50.049 --> 30:51.417
exactly what Heather
disclosed to you.

30:51.450 --> 30:54.420
We told everything
to Skip Peterson.

30:54.453 --> 30:56.255
Mm-hmm. We're talking to him
right now too.

30:57.990 --> 31:01.093
I don't need you to tell me
this thing is blowing up.

31:01.127 --> 31:03.896
Hash tag "What else
did Skip skip?" is trending.

31:05.197 --> 31:06.532
I'm just as hurt by this
as you are.

31:06.565 --> 31:09.435
Look, our case
is collapsing.

31:09.468 --> 31:10.903
You took this on air.

31:10.937 --> 31:14.406
Now you need to give us
anything that you have

31:14.440 --> 31:15.942
that can corroborate
Heather's story.

31:15.975 --> 31:18.044
Your notes,
your interviews.

31:18.077 --> 31:19.278
I can't do that.

31:19.311 --> 31:21.047
We're way past
the coy shtick, Skip.

31:21.080 --> 31:22.381
You don't get it.
I can't corroborate,

31:22.414 --> 31:24.050
because I don't have
anything to do so with.

31:24.083 --> 31:26.185
Come on, you must have
talked to the boys?

31:26.218 --> 31:27.553
To people who saw
Heather the next day?

31:27.586 --> 31:29.288
- The school?
- No.

31:29.321 --> 31:32.658
I talked to Professor Dillon
and Heather, in that order.

31:34.961 --> 31:37.463
Isn't investigating
the main component

31:37.496 --> 31:39.098
of investigative journalism?

31:39.131 --> 31:42.301
Three boys have been arrested
and arraigned.

31:42.334 --> 31:45.437
Their reputations damaged,
possibly beyond repair.

31:45.471 --> 31:47.706
Now, I know that
that's on us, too, but--

31:47.739 --> 31:49.475
20/20 hindsight's easy.

31:49.508 --> 31:51.277
You sound like my producer.

31:51.310 --> 31:53.179
Should I have talked to them?
Obviously, yes.

31:53.212 --> 31:54.180
So why didn't you?

31:54.213 --> 31:55.681
Because I was protecting
Heather.

31:55.714 --> 31:56.848
She was terrified
of reprisals.

31:56.882 --> 32:00.519
And given Hudson's history,
she had every right to be.

32:00.552 --> 32:02.388
I found Heather
to be very credible.

32:02.421 --> 32:04.490
I have daughters her age.

32:04.523 --> 32:06.725
I have to say, I feel
gratified in some small way

32:06.758 --> 32:10.029
I helped start a dialogue about
the outrage of campus rape.

32:10.062 --> 32:11.998
(woman) Skip, five minutes.
- Then why didn't you

32:12.031 --> 32:13.632
start that dialogue
with a story that was true?

32:13.665 --> 32:17.069
Because most other stories
are more complicated.

32:17.103 --> 32:18.971
They're he-said, she-said.

32:19.005 --> 32:20.706
Heather's story
checked every box.

32:20.739 --> 32:23.409
Callous administration.
Entitled, white frat boy jocks.

32:23.442 --> 32:25.544
The pack mentality
gang-bang aspect.

32:25.577 --> 32:27.246
That's the story
I've been looking for.

32:27.279 --> 32:29.015
If we hadn't grabbed it,
someone else would have.

32:29.048 --> 32:30.649
Damn the consequences,
right?

32:30.682 --> 32:32.584
Don't blame the messenger,
blame the audience.

32:32.618 --> 32:34.120
Campus rape is
so commonplace,

32:34.153 --> 32:35.754
it doesn't even rise
to the level of news.

32:35.787 --> 32:38.590
Look what it took
to get anyone to even care.

32:38.624 --> 32:42.394
I'd love to do this all day,
but I have a retraction to tape.

32:42.428 --> 32:44.430
Let's go, guys.
Let's do it.

32:46.232 --> 32:48.667
I went on a date with Brian.

32:48.700 --> 32:50.436
We got a little drunk.

32:50.469 --> 32:53.639
Then we made our way
back to the frat.

32:53.672 --> 32:57.743
I thought he liked me,
but it went wrong.

32:57.776 --> 32:59.478
It was horrible.

32:59.511 --> 33:01.147
Focus on the facts.

33:01.180 --> 33:04.250
Did Brian lead you
into a dark room

33:04.283 --> 33:07.019
where three of
his brothers were waiting?

33:07.053 --> 33:09.021
His room was dark,

33:09.055 --> 33:12.191
but it was empty.

33:12.224 --> 33:14.360
At first.

33:14.393 --> 33:17.096
So Connor Howell and Lance
Mosconi weren't waiting there?

33:18.697 --> 33:21.067
Connor came in later.
I'm positive of that.

33:21.100 --> 33:22.301
And Lance?

33:22.334 --> 33:24.670
I don't know.

33:26.838 --> 33:29.408
I know he was outside,
but it was dark.

33:29.441 --> 33:33.412
I was drunk, confused.

33:33.445 --> 33:35.047
Confused about what?

33:38.417 --> 33:40.752
When Heather came to me,
she couldn't even articulate

33:40.786 --> 33:42.654
what had been done to her.

33:42.688 --> 33:44.823
That's how deep the culturally
imposed self-blame goes.

33:44.856 --> 33:49.195
Okay, what exactly
did she articulate?

33:49.228 --> 33:52.098
She told me
she'd been assaulted.

33:52.131 --> 33:54.166
Did she say
she was gang-raped?

33:54.200 --> 33:57.269
It was obvious
she'd been through hell.

33:57.303 --> 33:59.838
Professor Dillon told me
that I was so traumatized,

33:59.871 --> 34:03.075
it would take a while for me
to process what had happened.

34:03.875 --> 34:07.213
Heather...

34:07.246 --> 34:09.148
Did Brian Mackey rape you?

34:11.417 --> 34:12.784
I was drunk.

34:14.320 --> 34:17.289
He started
to have sex with me.

34:17.323 --> 34:20.426
He moved really fast.

34:20.459 --> 34:22.694
Did you move with him?

34:22.728 --> 34:25.331
I guess...

34:25.364 --> 34:28.400
In the beginning.

34:28.434 --> 34:32.204
So it's possible
it was consensual.

34:32.238 --> 34:33.139
I'm not sure.

34:35.607 --> 34:37.276
I passed out.

34:38.910 --> 34:42.548
When I woke up,
Connor Howell was on top of me.

34:44.150 --> 34:46.352
He was raping me.

34:46.385 --> 34:48.120
I absolutely
didn't want that.

34:52.258 --> 34:54.860
I remember Brian
coming back into the room.

34:57.229 --> 34:58.730
And the others?

35:00.232 --> 35:01.767
That night is a blur.

35:04.370 --> 35:07.439
Guys harassing me
as I left.

35:09.308 --> 35:11.610
When I told
Professor Dillon that,

35:11.643 --> 35:14.746
she said they probably
all took a piece of me.

35:17.249 --> 35:18.884
Professor Dillon
told you that?

35:23.189 --> 35:25.257
Can you wait here a minute?

35:25.291 --> 35:27.759
I need to know exactly
what you told Heather.

35:27.793 --> 35:29.195
What she already knew.

35:29.228 --> 35:30.862
It was barbaric
the way they abused her,

35:30.896 --> 35:34.166
- taunted her, assaulted her.
- But she was raped.

35:34.200 --> 35:35.867
Right? Is that what
she told you?

35:35.901 --> 35:37.236
By how many men?

35:37.269 --> 35:38.604
What difference
does that make?

35:38.637 --> 35:40.306
- Excuse me?
(Dillon) She was assaulted.

35:40.339 --> 35:41.940
Does it matter by whom,

35:41.973 --> 35:43.775
for how long,
in which orifice?

35:43.809 --> 35:46.278
Yes! Yes! It matters.

35:46.312 --> 35:48.380
We are talking about
criminal charges

35:48.414 --> 35:49.948
based on specifics
of what happened.

35:49.981 --> 35:52.318
It doesn't matter
what happened to her.

35:52.351 --> 35:54.620
What matters is
it happens every day.

35:54.653 --> 35:57.389
And these frat boys strut around
like they're bulletproof.

35:57.423 --> 36:00.792
So a few of them finally
have to take responsibility?

36:00.826 --> 36:03.829
Good. This isn't about you
or these boys or this case.

36:03.862 --> 36:05.030
This is bigger
than any of us.

36:18.710 --> 36:19.411
Our story,
"Nightmare on Campus,"

36:20.312 --> 36:21.980
generated international
media attention

36:22.013 --> 36:24.216
and inspired
a long-overdue discussion

36:24.250 --> 36:26.452
about campus sexual assault.

36:26.485 --> 36:28.820
However, it has now come
to our attention

36:28.854 --> 36:31.223
that many of
the disturbing allegations

36:31.257 --> 36:33.392
were fabricated
by Heather Manning.

36:33.425 --> 36:34.926
Did I miss
the actual apology part?

36:34.960 --> 36:37.996
Like many of you,
I believed Heather.

36:38.029 --> 36:39.898
That was a mistake.

36:39.931 --> 36:41.533
We have asked
an independent ombudsman

36:41.567 --> 36:43.001
from the Medill
School of Journalism

36:43.034 --> 36:45.471
to investigate
and issue a report

36:45.504 --> 36:48.607
about what we can do differently
in the future.

36:48.640 --> 36:50.809
An independent
investigation.

36:50.842 --> 36:52.711
They're throwing the book
at themselves.

36:52.744 --> 36:55.981
Barba's hanging by a string and
Dodds is hanging you out to dry.

36:56.014 --> 36:58.284
I don't blame him.
We moved too fast.

36:58.317 --> 36:59.618
We didn't vet it
hard enough.

36:59.651 --> 37:01.787
It's not on us.
It's not even on that haircut.

37:01.820 --> 37:03.822
It's on Heather.
She straight-out lied to us.

37:03.855 --> 37:05.657
Fin.

37:05.691 --> 37:07.659
Heather, can I help you?

37:10.662 --> 37:12.364
Once the story
got out there,

37:12.398 --> 37:15.701
I had all these survivors
coming to me and disclosing,

37:15.734 --> 37:18.404
counting on me
to be their strength.

37:18.437 --> 37:20.972
I couldn't just
take back my story.

37:21.006 --> 37:23.509
But your story
wasn't true, Heather.

37:23.542 --> 37:25.977
Brian may think
he didn't rape me.

37:26.011 --> 37:27.946
But we were both drunk.

37:27.979 --> 37:30.349
Professor Dillon told me
that that means

37:30.382 --> 37:32.284
that I wasn't capable
of consenting.

37:32.318 --> 37:35.721
She also said
that once I passed out,

37:35.754 --> 37:37.656
there's no way to know
what happened to me.

37:37.689 --> 37:39.458
I could have
been gang-raped.

37:39.491 --> 37:42.694
But we can't make that case.

37:42.728 --> 37:43.962
What about Connor?

37:43.995 --> 37:46.365
I know he raped me.

37:46.398 --> 37:47.633
Brian left.

37:47.666 --> 37:51.002
And I was passed out.
I was half-naked.

37:51.036 --> 37:55.341
And then I came to
because Connor was raping me.

37:55.374 --> 37:57.876
Hard, violent.

38:01.613 --> 38:02.781
Did anybody else see?

38:02.814 --> 38:06.318
Yes. Brian came in.
He saw everything.

38:08.654 --> 38:11.089
And then he just turned
and walked away.

38:11.122 --> 38:12.624
Like you're doing now.

38:16.995 --> 38:18.897
I believe you, Heather.

38:19.998 --> 38:22.934
But a jury is going
to have reasonable doubt.

38:26.972 --> 38:29.641
So that's it?

38:29.675 --> 38:32.944
I have to go to school
every day and see my rapist?

38:34.012 --> 38:36.081
I'm sorry, Heather.

38:36.114 --> 38:39.885
I'm sorry about all of it.

38:39.918 --> 38:41.887
And if there was
something I could do

38:41.920 --> 38:44.490
to go back and change it,
I would.

38:44.523 --> 38:47.793
[crying]

38:47.826 --> 38:49.361
[quietly]
But at this point...

38:50.962 --> 38:53.599
There's nothing we can do.

39:00.606 --> 39:03.041
Your Honor, given
the collapse of this case,

39:03.074 --> 39:04.476
we move for a dismissal
of all charges

39:04.510 --> 39:05.877
against the four defendants.

39:05.911 --> 39:07.746
How say you, Mr. Barba?

39:07.779 --> 39:09.681
We are prepared
to drop the charges.

39:09.715 --> 39:12.050
(Judge Pepitone)
Against all four of the accused?

39:12.083 --> 39:14.486
Yes, Your Honor.
All four.

39:14.520 --> 39:19.057
Assuming no other holds,
you are free to go, gentlemen.

39:19.090 --> 39:20.859
Thank you,
Your Honor.

39:31.537 --> 39:33.004
[scoffs]

39:35.474 --> 39:39.044
I believed Heather.
I still believe Heather.

39:39.077 --> 39:42.047
We all know something horrible
happened to her that night,

39:42.080 --> 39:44.883
but until rape culture
changes in this country,

39:44.916 --> 39:47.085
none of us will be safe.

39:47.118 --> 39:50.556
And that was just part
of the outrage on campus today

39:50.589 --> 39:52.190
as students reacted
to the news

39:52.223 --> 39:54.526
that the D.A. has dropped
the charges

39:54.560 --> 39:55.927
against all four defendants

39:55.961 --> 39:57.929
in the Hudson University
gang-rape case.

39:57.963 --> 40:00.098
Meanwhile, an attorney
for the former defendants

40:00.131 --> 40:02.133
will be filing a lawsuit

40:02.167 --> 40:05.070
against Hudson University and
the NYPD early next week.

40:05.103 --> 40:06.171
Turn that off.

40:06.204 --> 40:08.707
Well, we should feel proud.

40:08.740 --> 40:10.208
Pumped up their ratings
for another week,

40:10.241 --> 40:12.043
and those boys will never get
their reputations back.

40:12.077 --> 40:14.112
Yeah, but that's the job,
Carisi.

40:14.145 --> 40:17.015
It's hard to know what actually
happened in cases like these.

40:17.048 --> 40:19.585
If you can't take that,
SVU isn't right for you.

40:19.618 --> 40:22.153
Nah, I get it.
I'm good here.

40:22.187 --> 40:24.089
Let's hope Liv is.

40:24.122 --> 40:26.625
Right now she's heading up
to Hudson U.

40:26.658 --> 40:30.161
Round three of the apology tour.

40:30.195 --> 40:31.763
Given everything
that's happened,

40:31.797 --> 40:35.233
I wanted to apologize
for my tone a few days back.

40:35.266 --> 40:37.135
We were both
taken advantage of,

40:37.168 --> 40:38.904
and we both
had blinders on.

40:38.937 --> 40:42.240
You know, it was
the perfect story.

40:42.273 --> 40:44.976
It confirmed all of
my preconceived notions.

40:45.010 --> 40:48.113
And that alone should have
made me approach it

40:48.146 --> 40:49.848
with more skepticism.

40:49.881 --> 40:51.683
And, to be honest,
I can't help but ask

40:51.717 --> 40:53.084
if I'd listened
to Heather

40:53.118 --> 40:54.720
instead of badgering her
with questions

40:54.753 --> 40:56.254
if this wouldn't have
ended differently.

40:56.287 --> 40:57.188
Maybe.

40:57.222 --> 40:59.925
Maybe she would have
told you the true story.

41:01.159 --> 41:05.463
Connor Howell
did actually rape Heather.

41:07.298 --> 41:11.236
You have a dangerous predator
on your campus.

41:11.269 --> 41:12.938
And now that he's
gotten away with it,

